server creation=node js+express
basic commands
1)creation of the package json=npm init
2)creation of node modules=npm i express

basic steps
1)creating a folder(bank server)
2)create package.json
3)install express
4)create index .js
5)import express inside the index.js
6)create an app using the express
7)set up port number
8)resolving http request
Get    - To get the data
    post   - To post the data
    put    - To update data partially
    patch  - To update data completely
    delete - To delete the data completely

9)HTTP response code
    1xx - Information
    2xx - Successfull
    3xx - Redirection
    4xx - Client error
    5xx - Server error
    
10)JWT Token
    Install JWT - npm i jsonwebtoken
    To generate a Token - sign()

11) Middleware 
    It comes in the middle of the request and response cycle of nodeJs execution proscess
        1) Application specific middleware - For the entire application
            -req,res,next
        2) Router specific middleware - validate token - verify() - jwtwebtoken
        
12)Database Integration
1)install mongoose-npm i mongoose

13)asynchronous function resolving-promise
1)resolve state-.then()
2)reject state-catch()

14)cors-cross origin resource sharing
install cors-npm i cors
port 4200(angular)-----request------>3000(node)

15)
asynchronous call - rxjs (reactive extension for javascript)

js-promise
ts-rxjs(library)
1)observable
a)resolved -subscribe()
b)reject-catch()








